  "text": "As with a number of the other signal transduction enzymes, however, caution must be taken in interpreting studies using broad-based inhibitors. Phospholipase C is known to exist as at least 10 isozymes characterized into three families: ␤, which are G protein linked; ␥, which are typically activated by tyrosine phosphorylation; and ␦, for which the activation process is yet to be determined [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, the activation mode for a given isozyme may vary among tissues [CITATION_2] .",
